<i>We're All Grown Up Now.</i>

6
00:01:30,440 --> 00:01:31,280
My...

7
00:01:31,360 --> 00:01:33,280
My son left his test paper here

8
00:01:33,360 --> 00:01:34,720
and asked me to pick it up.

9
00:01:36,320 --> 00:01:37,200
I see.

10
00:01:37,280 --> 00:01:39,800
Is your son in Grade 12 too?

11
00:01:39,880 --> 00:01:41,120
Yes, Grade 12.

12
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,560
Well, Grade 12 students
have tight schedules,

13
00:01:43,640 --> 00:01:45,200
so he asked me to get it for him.

14
00:01:53,920 --> 00:01:54,840
I'm sure.

15
00:01:54,920 --> 00:01:56,680
He's definitely not a student's parent.

16
00:01:56,760 --> 00:01:58,240
He said his son is in Grade 12,

17
00:01:58,320 --> 00:01:59,960
but he headed for the Grade 11 building.

18
00:02:00,040 --> 00:02:02,440
And he looked sneaky and guilty.

19
00:02:02,520 --> 00:02:04,120
A lot of things have gone missing lately.

20
00:02:04,200 --> 00:02:05,320
It must be his doing.

21
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:07,640
The lock on the west gate is broken.

22
00:02:07,720 --> 00:02:09,120
It hasn't been fixed yet.

23
00:02:09,199 --> 00:02:10,880
And he came from that direction.

24
00:02:10,960 --> 00:02:12,880
There is a good chance
he will leave from there.

25
00:02:12,960 --> 00:02:14,360
Sirs, please go catch him.

26
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:15,920
Go check it out.

27
00:02:16,760 --> 00:02:17,920
I'll leave first.

28
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:19,920
Let me know if anything happens, sir.

29
00:02:24,760 --> 00:02:25,840
Gu Ran?

30
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:29,280
You have no idea

31
00:02:29,360 --> 00:02:30,880
how good my sixth sense is.

32
00:02:30,960 --> 00:02:33,040
I could tell he was not a good man,

33
00:02:33,120 --> 00:02:34,760
so I was extra cautious.

34
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:36,560
You're not an idiot.

35
00:02:36,640 --> 00:02:38,160
You didn't expose him to his face.

36
00:02:38,240 --> 00:02:39,320
Of course.

37
00:02:40,120 --> 00:02:41,360
I've reached my house. Bye.

38
00:02:42,960 --> 00:02:44,160
Jiang Jia.

39
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:50,400
You actually have a lot of strengths.

40
00:02:52,440 --> 00:02:53,480
Like what?

41
00:02:55,120 --> 00:02:56,240
You're brave

42
00:02:56,320 --> 00:02:57,720
and always righteous.

43
00:02:58,760 --> 00:03:00,480
You're calm and not reckless.

44
00:03:04,280 --> 00:03:05,520
It took you two nights

45
00:03:05,600 --> 00:03:07,040
to make that up, didn't it?

46
00:03:08,040 --> 00:03:09,080
No.

47
00:03:09,160 --> 00:03:12,120
When we talk about strengths,

48
00:03:12,200 --> 00:03:14,560
people always immediately think

49
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,360
of extraordinary intelligence

50
00:03:16,440 --> 00:03:17,920
and innate talent.

51
00:03:19,160 --> 00:03:20,480
We believe

52
00:03:20,560 --> 00:03:23,760
everyone possesses courage and composure.

53
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,240
That's actually not true.

54
00:03:26,080 --> 00:03:27,400
Does everyone stand up

55
00:03:27,480 --> 00:03:29,080
when they see injustice?

56
00:03:29,760 --> 00:03:30,880
No.

57
00:03:30,960 --> 00:03:32,960
Does everyone empathize with the weak?

58
00:03:33,440 --> 00:03:34,640
Also no.

59
00:03:35,360 --> 00:03:37,800
Your uncommon bravery and righteousness

60
00:03:37,880 --> 00:03:39,320
are really hard to come by.

61
00:03:40,080 --> 00:03:41,000
Aren't they strengths?

62
00:03:46,640 --> 00:03:47,680
You're such a sweet talker.

63
00:03:47,760 --> 00:03:48,960
Tell me more next time.

64
00:03:49,520 --> 00:03:50,880
You enjoy the praise, don't you?

65
00:04:11,920 --> 00:04:13,120
JIANG JIA, GRADE 12, CLASS 2

66
00:04:14,760 --> 00:04:18,120
TARGET FIELD OF STUDY, REPORTER

67
00:04:23,360 --> 00:04:24,240
TEACHING BUILDING B

68
00:04:24,320 --> 00:04:25,960
<i>Are you aiming for East China University?</i>

69
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:27,320
Yes.

70
00:04:27,400 --> 00:04:28,640
That's the same as Lurang.

71
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:30,440
He told me that he wants to go there too.

72
00:04:32,840 --> 00:04:34,400
Let me look at your report card.

73
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:37,000
If you want to go there,

74
00:04:37,080 --> 00:04:39,920
you need to get at least 110 in math

75
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,280
even if you can score
consistently above 135 in English.

76
00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:44,800
You still need to work harder in math.

77
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,680
Feel free to ask me
if you have trouble with math.

78
00:04:48,520 --> 00:04:50,240
Okay. Thank you, Mr. Lin.

79
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:54,240
By the way,

80
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:57,640
English is your strong suit.

81
00:04:57,720 --> 00:04:59,680
Taking the autonomous admission exam

82
00:04:59,760 --> 00:05:01,160
will give you an advantage.

83
00:05:01,240 --> 00:05:03,240
Although East China University
is not included,

84
00:05:03,320 --> 00:05:05,120
there are still some good schools.

85
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:06,480
Bring it home and take a look.

86
00:05:13,080 --> 00:05:16,280
2015 CHENGJING UNIVERSITY
AUTONOMOUS ADMISSION INTERVIEW

87
00:05:16,360 --> 00:05:18,880
{\an8}AUTONOMOUS ADMISSION EXAM

88
00:05:23,480 --> 00:05:24,360
Excuse me.

89
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,400
Do you have a pen?

90
00:05:25,920 --> 00:05:27,480
-Hold on.
-Thank you.

91
00:05:27,560 --> 00:05:29,320
2015 CHENGJING UNIVERSITY
AUTONOMOUS ADMISSION INTERVIEW

92
00:05:29,400 --> 00:05:30,560
-Here you go.
-Thank you.

93
00:05:35,840 --> 00:05:36,680
Thank you.

94
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:37,600
You're welcome.

95
00:05:38,680 --> 00:05:40,200
Which school are you from?

96
00:05:40,280 --> 00:05:41,840
Jiangyi's First High School.
What about you?

97
00:05:41,920 --> 00:05:43,520
I'm from Suyang No. 1 High School.

98
00:05:44,800 --> 00:05:46,280
Suyang No. 1 High School?

99
00:05:47,440 --> 00:05:51,280
Then do you know Zhang Lurang

100
00:05:51,360 --> 00:05:52,880
in Grade 12?

101
00:05:52,960 --> 00:05:53,880
Zhang Lurang?

102
00:05:54,520 --> 00:05:55,840
I get it.

103
00:05:55,920 --> 00:05:58,400
Zhang Lurang was studying in Jiangyi
before he transferred.

104
00:05:58,480 --> 00:05:59,320
It must be your school.

105
00:06:01,280 --> 00:06:02,880
He sure has a lot of influence.

106
00:06:02,960 --> 00:06:05,640
Do you know anything else about him?

107
00:06:05,720 --> 00:06:06,600
Not really.

108
00:06:06,680 --> 00:06:08,400
He usually keeps a low profile.

109
00:06:11,320 --> 00:06:12,840
Are you trying

110
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:14,760
to find out his phone number?

111
00:06:15,280 --> 00:06:17,000
I can't help you with that.

112
00:06:17,080 --> 00:06:19,720
He doesn't even accept gifts from girls.

113
00:06:19,800 --> 00:06:22,120
He seems completely focused on studying.

114
00:06:23,720 --> 00:06:25,560
You should give up on him.

115
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,160
You are

116
00:06:36,520 --> 00:06:38,120
really obsessed with him, aren't you?

117
00:06:39,120 --> 00:06:41,040
This photo editing looks so real.

118
00:06:41,120 --> 00:06:42,480
My deskmate did the same too.

119
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:43,880
But his eyes turned out crooked.

120
00:06:46,320 --> 00:06:47,720
Next, Su Zaizai.

121
00:06:48,320 --> 00:06:49,480
Is Su Zaizai here?

122
00:06:49,560 --> 00:06:50,520
I'm coming.

123
00:06:50,600 --> 00:06:51,520
Good luck.

124
00:06:51,600 --> 00:06:55,560
AUTONOMOUS ADMISSION EXAM

125
00:06:57,000 --> 00:06:58,960
I was a bit nervous at first.

126
00:06:59,040 --> 00:07:00,400
But I felt better after a while.

127
00:07:00,480 --> 00:07:02,560
I answered all of the teachers' questions.

128
00:07:02,640 --> 00:07:03,760
<i>I'm glad to hear that.</i>

129
00:07:03,840 --> 00:07:05,760
<i>Zaizai, what time is your bus?</i>

130
00:07:05,840 --> 00:07:08,040
<i>Gu Ran, Guan Fang, and I
are eating near the bus station.</i>

131
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:09,120
<i>We can pick you up.</i>

132
00:07:10,400 --> 00:07:11,760
There are still more than two hours

133
00:07:11,840 --> 00:07:13,200
before the bus leaves from Suyang.

134
00:07:13,840 --> 00:07:14,720
That gives me time

135
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:16,920
to visit Rangrang's school while I'm here.

136
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,680
<i>But he can't use his phone.</i>

137
00:07:18,760 --> 00:07:20,040
<i>He won't know you're there.</i>

138
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:21,680
<i>Gu Ran, don't eavesdrop.</i>

139
00:07:21,760 --> 00:07:23,680
<i>It's not eavesdropping
if you're on speaker.</i>

140
00:07:25,320 --> 00:07:26,880
It doesn't matter if he doesn't know.

141
00:07:26,960 --> 00:07:28,240
I just want to take a look.

142
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:30,480
I have to go now. Bye.

143
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:39,040
SUYANG NO. 1 HIGH SCHOOL

144
00:07:43,520 --> 00:07:45,080
SUYANG NO. 1 HIGH SCHOOL

145
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:55,200
TENTH PLACE, ZHANG LURANG

146
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:57,920
HONOR ROLL

147
00:07:58,800 --> 00:07:59,720
Sir.

148
00:07:59,800 --> 00:08:01,280
Can you help me take a picture?

149
00:08:03,400 --> 00:08:04,840
You're not from this school, are you?

150
00:08:04,920 --> 00:08:06,120
No, I'm not.

151
00:08:06,200 --> 00:08:07,520
But my friend studies here.

152
00:08:07,600 --> 00:08:09,480
Then I'll make sure I take a nice photo.

153
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,800
You can send it to him later.

154
00:08:17,400 --> 00:08:18,320
Thank you.

155
00:08:23,360 --> 00:08:24,240
Don't stand there.

156
00:08:24,320 --> 00:08:26,240
Pictures come out better
with the view over there.

157
00:08:26,320 --> 00:08:27,400
It's okay.

158
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,040
I'll stand here.

159
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:34,360
TENTH PLACE, ZHANG LURANG

160
00:08:34,440 --> 00:08:35,720
Thank you.

161
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:41,919
Su Zaizai.

162
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,760
Rangrang?

163
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:49,640
It's not the weekend. Why are you here?

164
00:08:50,960 --> 00:08:52,480
Gu Ran called Luli and said

165
00:08:52,560 --> 00:08:53,720
you came to our school.

166
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:54,920
I happened to be nearby.

167
00:08:55,480 --> 00:08:57,320
So I rushed over
to see if you were still here.

168
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:01,160
Gu Ran sure sends news fast.

169
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:04,640
It has been a while. I...

170
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:08,720
We miss you.

171
00:09:11,320 --> 00:09:12,360
It has been a while.

172
00:09:15,000 --> 00:09:16,680
You mentioned the school in your letters.

173
00:09:16,760 --> 00:09:18,240
Now that I've come to see it,

174
00:09:18,320 --> 00:09:19,880
it feels as if I've been here before.

175
00:09:19,960 --> 00:09:21,000
It's mystifying.

176
00:09:23,000 --> 00:09:24,120
Do you want to look inside?

177
00:09:28,720 --> 00:09:30,360
Rangrang, is that the tree

178
00:09:30,440 --> 00:09:31,920
that you said is even older than us?

179
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:35,960
Actually, there is
nothing special about it.

180
00:09:36,040 --> 00:09:37,440
It's just that when I just arrived,

181
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:39,720
I wanted to tell you about everything.

182
00:09:42,280 --> 00:09:44,240
Then you should write more.

183
00:09:44,320 --> 00:09:45,400
I don't mind reading it.

184
00:09:50,280 --> 00:09:52,240
Gu Ran said you're here

185
00:09:52,320 --> 00:09:54,120
for an autonomous admission interview.

186
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,160
Yes.

187
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:59,440
My current grades are not good enough

188
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:00,880
to get into East China University.

189
00:10:00,960 --> 00:10:02,920
I think I should play it safe.

190
00:10:04,760 --> 00:10:05,640
That's good too.

191
00:10:09,120 --> 00:10:11,160
Rangrang, I didn't expect you

192
00:10:11,240 --> 00:10:13,360
to be so popular in Suyang too.

193
00:10:13,440 --> 00:10:15,960
They must be wondering who I am

194
00:10:16,040 --> 00:10:17,520
and why I am with you.

195
00:10:22,960 --> 00:10:24,360
Rangrang,

196
00:10:24,440 --> 00:10:26,120
I took the autonomous admission interview

197
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:28,160
not because I wanted
to give up on East China University.

198
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:31,160
I just don't want
to gamble everything on the NCEE

199
00:10:31,240 --> 00:10:33,080
and make everyone worry about me.

200
00:10:33,640 --> 00:10:34,840
After I get back to Jiangyi,

201
00:10:34,920 --> 00:10:36,800
I'll study even harder.

202
00:10:36,880 --> 00:10:38,520
But whether we can get

203
00:10:38,600 --> 00:10:40,000
into the same university or not,

204
00:10:40,080 --> 00:10:41,800
you should pursue your own goals.

205
00:10:42,360 --> 00:10:43,760
Let's not give up our dreams

206
00:10:43,840 --> 00:10:45,280
for other people.

207
00:10:45,360 --> 00:10:46,840
I don't like that.

208
00:10:46,920 --> 00:10:48,280
Becoming better together

209
00:10:48,360 --> 00:10:49,680
is the coolest thing.

210
00:10:54,280 --> 00:10:55,560
All right.

211
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:57,120
You too.

212
00:10:58,200 --> 00:10:59,520
No matter what the result is,

213
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:01,320
it's okay if we give it our best.

214
00:11:21,920 --> 00:11:24,400
100 DAYS TO THE NCEE!

215
00:11:45,080 --> 00:11:46,040
Before we begin,

216
00:11:46,120 --> 00:11:48,120
I have two pieces of good news to share.

217
00:11:48,200 --> 00:11:49,400
Our class's Xu Mingliang

218
00:11:49,480 --> 00:11:51,760
has passed and received
a guaranteed admission offer

219
00:11:51,840 --> 00:11:53,240
from the University of South China.

220
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:54,600
Also, Wang Nan,

221
00:11:54,680 --> 00:11:56,120
Su Zaizai, and Chen Min

222
00:11:56,200 --> 00:11:58,080
have passed the autonomous admission exam.

223
00:11:58,160 --> 00:12:00,600
You can say your hard work has paid off.

224
00:12:00,680 --> 00:12:01,920
Congratulations.

225
00:12:03,680 --> 00:12:04,960
Okay, let's start our lesson.

226
00:12:20,960 --> 00:12:22,120
Don't you think

227
00:12:22,200 --> 00:12:23,400
it's too early to give up now?

228
00:12:25,000 --> 00:12:26,160
As long as you work hard,

229
00:12:26,240 --> 00:12:27,480
you can always find the answers

230
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,920
to the textbooks' problems.

231
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,720
But you will encounter
many difficult problems

232
00:12:31,800 --> 00:12:34,160
in your life in the future.

233
00:12:34,240 --> 00:12:35,680
Those have no standard answers.

234
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:39,280
Of course, you may not understand

235
00:12:39,880 --> 00:12:41,680
what I'm saying now.

236
00:12:42,240 --> 00:12:43,560
But years later,

237
00:12:44,280 --> 00:12:46,200
you will definitely miss this hot summer.

238
00:12:48,000 --> 00:12:49,200
So students,

239
00:12:49,760 --> 00:12:50,880
let's cheer up

240
00:12:51,480 --> 00:12:53,360
and don't do anything you will regret.

241
00:12:53,440 --> 00:12:55,360
It's never too late

242
00:12:55,440 --> 00:12:56,920
to start working hard.

243
00:12:57,000 --> 00:12:58,760
Now is the best moment.

244
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:06,640
<i>Rangrang, Mr. Lin is indeed your uncle.</i>

245
00:13:06,720 --> 00:13:07,840
<i>His words</i>

246
00:13:07,920 --> 00:13:10,560
<i>have ignited passion in all of us.</i>

247
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:13,360
<i>I've never felt so motivated before.</i>

248
00:13:19,960 --> 00:13:22,280
<i>Rangrang, this will be my last letter.</i>

249
00:13:22,360 --> 00:13:23,840
<i>As the NCEE approaches,</i>

250
00:13:23,920 --> 00:13:25,880
<i>time suddenly feels like sand</i>

251
00:13:25,960 --> 00:13:27,800
<i>slipping through my fingers,</i>

252
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:29,560
<i>gone in the blink of an eye.</i>

253
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,960
<i>I've even been eating</i>

254
00:13:31,040 --> 00:13:32,000
<i>a lot faster.</i>

255
00:13:32,080 --> 00:13:33,280
GUAN'S DESSERT SHOP

256
00:13:33,360 --> 00:13:35,080
Stop studying. Quick.

257
00:13:35,160 --> 00:13:36,120
Eat your food.

258
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:37,400
Eat some wontons.

259
00:13:39,960 --> 00:13:41,400
<i>I'm really tired.</i>

260
00:13:42,320 --> 00:13:43,680
<i>But when I think</i>

261
00:13:43,760 --> 00:13:45,960
<i>that you're also working hard
someplace else,</i>

262
00:13:46,040 --> 00:13:47,560
<i>I feel like I can keep persevering.</i>

263
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,240
<i>I have good news.</i>

264
00:13:54,320 --> 00:13:55,680
<i>My math scores</i>

265
00:13:55,760 --> 00:13:57,960
<i>have been consistently above 100.</i>

266
00:13:58,040 --> 00:14:00,760
<i>Rangrang, I believe in miracles again.</i>

267
00:14:01,720 --> 00:14:03,280
TO ZHANG LURANG

268
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:06,000
<i>See? You clearly can do it.</i>

269
00:14:08,920 --> 00:14:09,800
Luli.

270
00:14:09,880 --> 00:14:11,200
Lurang.

271
00:14:12,320 --> 00:14:14,120
<i>Sometimes, taking one more step forward</i>

272
00:14:14,200 --> 00:14:16,200
<i>doesn't seem to be that difficult.</i>

273
00:14:16,960 --> 00:14:18,120
<i>The countdown in our class</i>

274
00:14:18,200 --> 00:14:19,480
<i>is updated every day.</i>

275
00:14:21,240 --> 00:14:22,960
<i>Throwing coins into the wishing fountain</i>

276
00:14:23,040 --> 00:14:25,440
<i>has become a popular trend in the school.</i>

277
00:14:25,520 --> 00:14:27,000
<i>I don't believe in these things.</i>

278
00:14:27,480 --> 00:14:30,120
<i>But I think that if you were here,</i>

279
00:14:30,200 --> 00:14:31,880
<i>you would be enthusiastic about it.</i>

280
00:14:32,600 --> 00:14:34,040
<i>So I decided to throw a coin as well.</i>

281
00:14:35,280 --> 00:14:37,160
<i>Many people attribute this experience</i>

282
00:14:37,240 --> 00:14:39,120
<i>to life-changing significance.</i>

283
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:40,080
<i>But I just hope...</i>

284
00:14:40,160 --> 00:14:41,040
