FOR THE FIRST HIGH SCHOOL
AFFILIATED TO JIANGYI UNIVERSITY

304
00:16:16,720 --> 00:16:18,160
-Let's take a picture together.
-Okay.

305
00:16:22,680 --> 00:16:24,120
Let's take another one. Hey!

306
00:16:24,720 --> 00:16:26,160
Su Zaizai, let's take a picture.

307
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,120
-Here.
-Sure.

308
00:16:29,280 --> 00:16:30,320
I wasn't ready.

309
00:16:31,560 --> 00:16:32,400
Hey.

310
00:16:33,520 --> 00:16:34,840
I've taken pictures with them.

311
00:16:34,920 --> 00:16:35,760
Let's take one.

312
00:16:35,840 --> 00:16:37,160
You did? Okay.

313
00:16:41,000 --> 00:16:41,840
Okay, all done.

314
00:16:41,920 --> 00:16:42,800
Wait a minute.

315
00:16:42,880 --> 00:16:44,040
My eyes were closed.

316
00:16:44,120 --> 00:16:45,040
Let's take one more.

317
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:46,080
Fine.

318
00:16:50,280 --> 00:16:51,200
There you go.

319
00:16:53,040 --> 00:16:54,960
It's blurry. Let's take another one.

320
00:16:55,040 --> 00:16:56,000
For a guy,

321
00:16:56,080 --> 00:16:57,480
why are you so fussy about a picture?

322
00:16:57,560 --> 00:16:58,400
No more.

323
00:16:58,480 --> 00:16:59,960
{\an8}Guan Fang, let's take a picture.

324
00:17:00,040 --> 00:17:02,040
-No!
-Come on. Let's take another one.

325
00:17:02,120 --> 00:17:03,000
You're so annoying!

326
00:17:03,080 --> 00:17:04,079
Quick. Just one more.

327
00:17:04,160 --> 00:17:05,359
-No.
-What are you doing?

328
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:07,400
Stop it.

329
00:17:07,480 --> 00:17:08,440
-Go away.
-It looks nice.

330
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,000
Let's take another one.

331
00:17:10,079 --> 00:17:12,160
-Please.
-Let's do it.

332
00:17:12,240 --> 00:17:13,560
Okay.

333
00:17:13,640 --> 00:17:15,040
How about the three of us together?

334
00:17:15,119 --> 00:17:16,280
Hello, Rangrang.

335
00:17:16,359 --> 00:17:19,040
-Let's take one more!
-Guess where we are now.

336
00:17:19,119 --> 00:17:20,480
<i>-At school?</i>
-You deserved that.

337
00:17:21,400 --> 00:17:23,000
It's the graduation ceremony.

338
00:17:23,079 --> 00:17:24,960
All the graduates are here.

339
00:17:28,920 --> 00:17:30,040
It's strange though.

340
00:17:31,280 --> 00:17:33,320
Today, I'm suddenly reluctant

341
00:17:33,960 --> 00:17:36,080
to leave the school
that I used to be sick of.

342
00:17:37,840 --> 00:17:40,160
And the stern dean

343
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,920
has been smiling all day today.

344
00:17:44,040 --> 00:17:44,920
Rangrang,

345
00:17:45,880 --> 00:17:47,000
happy graduation.

346
00:17:47,080 --> 00:17:48,240
Su Zaizai.

347
00:17:58,080 --> 00:17:59,040
Happy graduation.

348
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:01,920
-Lurang!
-Lurang!

349
00:18:08,520 --> 00:18:10,560
It has been so long! This is so sudden.

350
00:18:11,240 --> 00:18:12,280
I wanted to come back

351
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:13,600
for your graduation ceremony.

352
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,240
You're a great friend.

353
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,440
You've gotten thinner.

354
00:18:17,960 --> 00:18:19,760
But you're still just as handsome.

355
00:18:21,080 --> 00:18:22,920
Zhang Lurang, perfect timing.

356
00:18:23,000 --> 00:18:24,320
Let me take a group photo for you.

357
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:25,240
Good idea. Come on.

358
00:18:25,320 --> 00:18:26,280
Come.

359
00:18:31,040 --> 00:18:32,520
Stand closer together.

360
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:34,280
I'll start counting.

361
00:18:34,360 --> 00:18:35,400
Three.

362
00:18:35,480 --> 00:18:36,640
Two.

363
00:18:36,720 --> 00:18:37,720
One.

364
00:18:37,800 --> 00:18:39,000
-Cheese!
-Cheese!

365
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:44,040
I'm not bragging here.

366
00:18:44,120 --> 00:18:46,360
Grandma's new pineapple shaved ice
is really amazing.

367
00:18:46,440 --> 00:18:47,480
You guys have to try it.

368
00:18:49,240 --> 00:18:51,160
Grandma, Gu Ran and the others are here.

369
00:18:51,240 --> 00:18:52,240
GUAN'S DESSERT SHOP

370
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:53,280
Grandma?

371
00:18:58,640 --> 00:18:59,560
Grandma.

372
00:19:01,240 --> 00:19:02,160
Did she go out?

373
00:19:03,320 --> 00:19:04,720
But the shop isn't locked up.

374
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:06,800
Guan Fang!

375
00:19:07,560 --> 00:19:08,520
Hurry to the hospital.

376
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:10,200
Your grandma fell and was unconscious.

377
00:19:10,280 --> 00:19:11,840
The ambulance left just a while ago.

378
00:19:13,360 --> 00:19:14,720
Sir, which hospital?

379
00:19:14,800 --> 00:19:16,000
-The People's Hospital.
-Thank you!

380
00:19:16,080 --> 00:19:18,440
GUAN'S DESSERT SHOP

381
00:19:20,600 --> 00:19:21,480
Excuse me.

382
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,560
How is the elderly person
who was just brought in?

383
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:25,520
-I'm her family.
-They're still conducting tests.

384
00:19:25,600 --> 00:19:27,160
How is she now?

385
00:19:27,240 --> 00:19:29,400
We're currently trying
to contact Chen Lan's family.

386
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:31,200
Okay.

387
00:19:31,280 --> 00:19:32,600
I'm Chen Lan's family.

388
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:35,720
Ranran, what are you doing here?

389
00:19:35,800 --> 00:19:36,720
Mom,

390
00:19:36,800 --> 00:19:38,000
he's my friend.

391
00:19:40,480 --> 00:19:41,560
Where are your parents?

392
00:19:42,280 --> 00:19:44,240
It's just me. She's my grandma.

393
00:19:44,320 --> 00:19:46,640
Ms. Chen, how is his grandma doing?

394
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,840
The preliminary diagnosis
is a ruptured spleen

395
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:50,160
and hemorrhagic shock.

396
00:19:50,240 --> 00:19:51,440
She's undergoing some tests.

397
00:19:51,520 --> 00:19:52,880
She needs immediate surgery.

398
00:19:55,080 --> 00:19:57,560
I'll explain the procedure
and risks of the surgery to you first.

399
00:19:57,640 --> 00:19:59,040
Then you can sign the consent form.

400
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:02,240
Come with me.

401
00:20:06,080 --> 00:20:07,360
We'll wait here.

402
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:11,480
And then complications may arise,

403
00:20:11,560 --> 00:20:14,000
{\an8}such as bleeding,

404
00:20:14,080 --> 00:20:15,760
gallbladder dysfunction,
bile duct stricture,

405
00:20:15,840 --> 00:20:17,440
and hepatic dysfunction.

406
00:20:18,200 --> 00:20:19,960
This is a common surgery, right?

407
00:20:20,640 --> 00:20:21,560
Yes.

408
00:20:22,120 --> 00:20:23,920
Are there risks during the surgery?

409
00:20:24,480 --> 00:20:26,480
All surgeries have risks

410
00:20:26,560 --> 00:20:28,400
and various unexpected situations
may occur.

411
00:20:29,520 --> 00:20:30,960
But we'll do our best.

412
00:20:31,040 --> 00:20:31,920
Thank you.

413
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:34,600
What else can I do?

414
00:20:36,000 --> 00:20:38,920
You're already doing a great job
staying calm at your age.

415
00:20:39,000 --> 00:20:40,160
After you sign this,

416
00:20:40,240 --> 00:20:42,080
you can wait outside the operating room.

417
00:20:51,120 --> 00:20:52,640
SIGNATURE OF NEXT OF KIN

418
00:20:53,960 --> 00:20:55,680
{\an8}I'll sign it right away.

419
00:20:59,720 --> 00:21:05,920
{\an8}SIGNATURE OF NEXT OF KIN: GUAN FANG

420
00:21:25,360 --> 00:21:26,560
Mom.

421
00:21:26,640 --> 00:21:28,360
The surgery has been quite successful.

422
00:21:28,440 --> 00:21:30,560
Your grandma will come out soon.

423
00:21:30,640 --> 00:21:33,040
But further observation is still needed.

424
00:21:33,800 --> 00:21:35,400
Thank you, doctor.

425
00:21:41,960 --> 00:21:42,960
Everything is okay now.

426
00:21:44,360 --> 00:21:45,240
Thank you.

427
00:22:18,600 --> 00:22:19,920
If you're sleepy, take a nap.

428
00:22:20,960 --> 00:22:22,120
It's okay.

429
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,160
I'm not sleepy.

430
00:22:41,320 --> 00:22:42,720
<i>She woke up at noon.</i>

431
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,440
But she's still feeling weary.

432
00:22:44,520 --> 00:22:45,880
She dozed off quickly.

433
00:22:46,520 --> 00:22:47,880
I'm glad she's awake.

434
00:22:47,960 --> 00:22:49,480
We won't be going inside then.

435
00:22:49,560 --> 00:22:51,200
We should let her get more rest.

436
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:58,000
Remember to pay the fees
and collect the medication.

437
00:22:58,080 --> 00:22:59,720
Okay, thank you.

438
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:05,800
You look like you haven't slept all night.

439
00:23:07,160 --> 00:23:08,400
You should get some sleep.

440
00:23:08,960 --> 00:23:09,880
I know my way around.

441
00:23:09,960 --> 00:23:11,600
We can handle the little things for you.

442
00:23:12,400 --> 00:23:14,480
Yes. You probably haven't eaten either.

443
00:23:15,080 --> 00:23:16,840
Rangrang and I will buy you some food.

444
00:23:19,520 --> 00:23:20,520
Thank you.

445
00:23:21,920 --> 00:23:23,200
Let's go.

446
00:23:23,280 --> 00:23:24,200
Go.

447
00:24:11,760 --> 00:24:13,440
It has only been just a few days.

448
00:24:15,320 --> 00:24:16,920
But your wrinkles have increased a lot.

449
00:24:21,960 --> 00:24:23,360
Why don't we buy

450
00:24:23,440 --> 00:24:25,480
those toners or creams
mentioned on television

451
00:24:25,560 --> 00:24:27,840
that disappear wrinkles immediately

452
00:24:27,920 --> 00:24:29,360
after use?

453
00:24:30,400 --> 00:24:32,160
Let's see if they work.

454
00:24:36,720 --> 00:24:38,200
It would be great if they did work.

455
00:24:45,520 --> 00:24:46,640
Grandma?

456
00:24:46,720 --> 00:24:47,640
You're awake.

457
00:24:47,720 --> 00:24:51,360
I thought

458
00:24:51,440 --> 00:24:54,600
I heard Gu Ran and the others talking.

459
00:24:54,680 --> 00:24:57,440
Yes, they will be here later.

460
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:03,520
Is the graduation ceremony over?

461
00:25:07,800 --> 00:25:12,000
Mr. Chen said they waited

462
00:25:12,080 --> 00:25:14,680
outside the school entrance

463
00:25:14,760 --> 00:25:18,560
on their children's graduation day.

464
00:25:18,640 --> 00:25:20,360
I didn't even know.

465
00:25:21,280 --> 00:25:23,960
And I couldn't go to pick you up.

466
00:25:29,440 --> 00:25:31,520
Your high school graduation ceremony

467
00:25:32,760 --> 00:25:35,160
only happens once.

468
00:25:37,560 --> 00:25:42,640
I had planned to close the shop early

469
00:25:42,720 --> 00:25:45,000
to attend it.

470
00:25:46,360 --> 00:25:47,440
But in the end,

471
00:25:48,320 --> 00:25:50,040
I couldn't make it.

472
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,920
Instead, you ended up coming

473
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:56,160
to the hospital

474
00:25:56,240 --> 00:25:58,720
and having to bustle around.

475
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:09,880
Time really flies.

476
00:26:11,760 --> 00:26:13,280
I always felt

477
00:26:13,960 --> 00:26:16,440
like you were shorter than me yesterday.

478
00:26:17,840 --> 00:26:19,360
But in the blink of an eye,

479
00:26:20,160 --> 00:26:22,800
you've grown so much.

480
00:26:24,600 --> 00:26:26,920
You've become an adult.

481
00:26:29,880 --> 00:26:30,800
Grandma,

482
00:26:31,840 --> 00:26:33,360
come send me off

483
00:26:33,440 --> 00:26:34,840
when the university semester starts.

484
00:26:36,080 --> 00:26:38,120
And when I find a job,

485
00:26:38,200 --> 00:26:40,080
you can pick me up and drop me off.

486
00:26:42,360 --> 00:26:43,640
By then,

487
00:26:43,720 --> 00:26:46,800
I probably won't be able to walk anymore.

488
00:26:48,120 --> 00:26:49,080
Then

489
00:26:49,840 --> 00:26:51,200
I'll be the one who picks you up.

490
00:26:51,680 --> 00:26:53,080
If that doesn't work,

491
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:54,160
I'll carry you on my back.

492
00:26:55,280 --> 00:26:57,200
That would be so tiring.

493
00:26:59,160 --> 00:27:00,760
But when I was little,

494
00:27:02,840 --> 00:27:05,000
didn't you always carry me like that too?

495
00:27:09,360 --> 00:27:10,280
Good.

496
00:27:12,000 --> 00:27:13,800
Good boy.

497
00:27:15,440 --> 00:27:16,400
Good.

498
00:27:21,280 --> 00:27:22,480
{\an8}Can she be discharged now?

499
00:27:23,120 --> 00:27:25,000
{\an8}I'll do the discharge paperwork in a bit.

500
00:27:25,080 --> 00:27:26,320
That's great.

501
00:27:26,840 --> 00:27:29,280
Have you seen how well Guan Fang
has been taking care of her?

502
00:27:30,920 --> 00:27:33,360
My mom used to compare me only to Lurang.

503
00:27:33,440 --> 00:27:34,400
Now, great.

504
00:27:34,480 --> 00:27:35,600
She will use Guan Fang too.

505
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:39,760
I always thought

506
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:42,120
I would become an adult

507
00:27:42,200 --> 00:27:43,240
once I turned 18.

508
00:27:44,560 --> 00:27:46,320
But recently, I've suddenly realized

509
00:27:46,400 --> 00:27:48,000
that being an adult

510
00:27:48,080 --> 00:27:49,800
means taking on responsibility.

511
00:27:51,720 --> 00:27:53,120
My grandma has had a hard life.

512
00:27:53,800 --> 00:27:56,560
It's my turn to protect her from now on.

513
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:00,200
I'm really glad to have you guys here.

514
00:28:03,320 --> 00:28:05,840
That means adults also need friends.

515
00:28:05,920 --> 00:28:07,520
Yes, they do.

516
00:28:08,200 --> 00:28:10,000
Because only with friends around

517
00:28:10,080 --> 00:28:12,440
can adults
temporarily not act like adults.

518
00:28:15,920 --> 00:28:17,800
The evening after the rain
is so beautiful.

519
00:28:20,280 --> 00:28:23,120
The weather tomorrow will be nice.

520
00:28:23,200 --> 00:28:24,880
Yes, I'm sure it will be.

521
00:28:53,600 --> 00:28:55,200
Rangrang, I'm home.

522
00:28:55,280 --> 00:28:57,640
You should go back and rest early.

523
00:28:58,600 --> 00:28:59,440
Su Zaizai.

524
00:29:03,000 --> 00:29:04,040
The weather

525
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:06,080
will be nice tomorrow.

526
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:09,240
You mentioned it earlier.

527
00:29:12,080 --> 00:29:13,120
So

528
00:29:14,560 --> 00:29:15,720
will you be free?

529
00:29:29,800 --> 00:29:31,280
<i>I'm really going to graduate.</i>

530
00:29:31,360 --> 00:29:33,400
<i>I just realized
how reluctant I am to leave.</i>

531
00:29:34,360 --> 00:29:36,040
<i>Actually, there is one thing</i>

532
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:37,320
<i>in high school</i>

533
00:29:37,400 --> 00:29:38,800
<i>that I have always regretted.</i>

534
00:29:39,520 --> 00:29:40,480
<i>That is,</i>

535
00:29:40,560 --> 00:29:41,560
<i>I never had the chance</i>

536
00:29:41,640 --> 00:29:44,160
<i>to experience being in the same class
as Rangrang.</i>

537
00:29:44,240 --> 00:29:45,320
<i>It's such a pity.</i>

538
00:29:47,120 --> 00:29:48,880
<i>I wanted to sit next to him</i>

539
00:29:48,960 --> 00:29:51,280
<i>and spend 12 hours with him every day</i>

540
00:29:51,360 --> 00:29:53,440
<i>from morning to evening.</i>

541
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:55,760
<i>Then I would pretend
to borrow a pen from him.</i>

542
00:29:56,280 --> 00:29:57,440
<i>And I would look over...</i>

543
00:29:58,680 --> 00:30:00,880
<i>Rangrang, what are you doing here?</i>

544
00:30:02,120 --> 00:30:03,200
<i>What are you recording?</i>

545
00:30:05,560 --> 00:30:07,240
<i>I'm recording precious memories</i>

546
00:30:07,320 --> 00:30:08,560
